	<h1 class="sustok">General Terms and Conditions</h1>
	<div class="container">
		<ul class="a">
			<p style="margin-bottom: 2%">Effective from 28th October 2021</p>
			<p style="margin-bottom: 2%">Loadeat Kft.</p>
			<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Subject matter of the contract, basic provisions</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-1">
    				<li id="1-1"><b>1.1.</b>The subject of this contract is to ensure the appearance of the Customer in the Internet reservation system developed by the service provider, and the transmission of reservations and requests for offers to the Customer.</li>
    				<li><b>1.2.</b> Definitions
						The Internet reservation system developed by the Service Provider and its associated sites:
						The set of Internet sites over which the Service Provider has control, either in its own right or by special agreement.
						<br>Customer: the person entitled to rent a table for a period of time, within the meaning of the legislation in force, for the purpose of the table to be displayed on the reservation system.
						<br>Guest: The third party who uses the reservation system to reserve a table or to request a table.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Rights and obligations of the Parties</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-2">
    				<li><b>2.1.</b> The Service Provider is obliged to display the Customer's table in the Internet reservation system on the basis of the data duly uploaded by the Customer on the administration interface.</li>
					<li><b>2.2.</b> The Service Provider shall forward to the Customer, in the manner and under the conditions set out in a separate chapter of the General Terms and Conditions <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('fejezet-3', true)">( Chapter III )</span>, the requests for quotations and reservations received via the system.</li>
					<li id="2-3"><b>2.3.</b> The Service Provider shall be entitled to inform the guests and third party visitors who are not guests, among the information displayed on the Internet, that the Service Provider is not a party to the contract for the purchase of the table, taking into account that the legal relationship for the use of the table is and can only be established between the parties using the table and the parties selling the table. It is also entitled to provide information on liability issues arising from this legal relationship,
					The Service Provider is also entitled to publish the guest's opinion after the table has been used, by filling in an online questionnaire as part of the reservation system, which facilitates an objective evaluation.</li>
					<li><b>2.4.</b> The Service Provider is entitled to send promotional and advertising material about its services and those of its partners to the e-mail address provided by the Customer.</li>
					<li><b>2.5.</b> The Service Provider is entitled to display the price list and package offer uploaded by the customer on the partner's pages.</li>
					<li><b>2.6.</b> The Service Provider is automatically entitled to suspend the display of the given apartment table on the day following the due date in the event of a breach of the obligation to pay the fee as defined in a separate chapter of the General Terms and Conditions, unless otherwise agreed.</li>
					<li><b>2.7.</b> The Service Provider shall be entitled to advertise the Customer's table or a specific table in its system in any manner whatsoever.</li>
					<li><b>2.8.</b> The Customer shall pay the consideration specified in a separate chapter of the General Terms and Conditions <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('fejezet-4', true)">( Chapter IV )</span>.</li>
					<li id="2-9"><b>2.9.</b> The Customer shall be obliged to ensure that the data on the administrative interface made available to him is correct, so that no contact details are displayed in the Customer's data or in internal messages (requests for quotations), nor shall he otherwise encourage the Guest to contact him directly. The Customer shall be entitled to approve table reservations received via the Service Provider's system exclusively via the Service Provider's system for the apartment price list and package offer indicated on the website.</li>
					<li><b>2.10.</b> The Customer shall immediately inform the Service Provider of any technical difficulties which may prevent or limit the performance of the contract, in particular any permanent or intermittent (expected to last more than 1 working day) lack of Internet connection, or any other factor which may prevent the proper use of the system.</li>
					<li id="2-11"><b>2.11.</b> In the event of a successful reservation, the Customer shall, if the reserved table cannot be provided to the Guest, provide the Guest with a table of the same or higher standard as a substitute service without any extra charge.
					The customer is obliged to respond to any request made through the service provider's system within 1 working day (in particular: table reservation, package reservation, request for an offer).</li>
					<li><b>2.12.</b> Price guarantee The customer may not give a lower price than the prices indicated in the service provider's system, nor in the system of other service providers, nor on his own website, nor in any other source, and must indicate all other promotions indicated on the service provider's system.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Table reservation and confirmation, bid</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-3">
    				<li><b>3.1.</b> Any guest may use the On-line reservation system without discrimination, subject to the rules of use, to request an offer or make a reservation.</li>
					<li><b>3.2.</b> The Service Provider shall notify the Customer by e-mail of the accommodation and related data which the Customer wishes to reserve.</li>
					<li><b>3.3.</b> The Service Provider shall forward the confirmation received to the Guest without delay (by e-mail) during the period of operation of the reservation system.</li>
					<li><b>3.4.</b> The service provider is entitled to contact the customer by telephone, SMS or any other means of communication with the customer with unanswered requests for quotations, room reservations and other information necessary for the operation of the system !</li>
					<li><b>3.5.</b> If the guest cancels the reservation before the scheduled time of the reservation with the cancellation conditions specified by the customer, the parties shall cancel the reservation from the system, with the simultaneous application of the legal consequences set out in clause <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('4-5', false)">4.5.</span> of the General Terms and Conditions. The Customer shall notify the Service Provider of the cancellation within 1 working day of the guest's notification, otherwise the table shall be considered to be occupied.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Terms of payment</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-4">
    				<li><b>4.1.</b> The Customer shall pay a commission on the consideration for the service specified in section <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('1-1', false)">1.1.</span> the rate of which is 12.5% + VAT on the net amount of the consideration for the services booked through the online reservation system provided by the Service Provider and the net amount of the services offered and implemented by the Customer, which the Customer may set at a higher percentage rate as desired.</li>
					<li><b>4.2.</b> The service provider shall send a monthly invoice for the commission of the table reservations mediated by him, if the total monthly value of the commission exceeds HUF 2000. If the customer does not dispute the use of the table within 1 working day, the Service Provider will consider it as approved.
					If the use of the table by the guest has not actually taken place, the customer shall be obliged to confirm this to the service provider within this period of 1 working day from the date of cancellation by the guest by means of a declaration of cancellation of the table or by other appropriate means, provided that this has not taken place through the service provider's system.</li>
					<li><b>4.3.</b> In the event of proven breach of contract by the Customer, as referred to in point <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('2-9', false)">2.9</span> of the General Terms and Conditions, the Service Provider shall be entitled to double the amount of the commission which the Customer has forfeited as a result of the deliberate circumvention of the system, which amount shall be deemed to be a compensation for damages and the payment of which shall not preclude the Service Provider from claiming from the Customer any damages in excess of this amount.</li>
					<li><b>4.4.</b> The Service Provider shall also be entitled to claim the commission due in the event of a reservation from the Customer in the event of the conditions set out in clause <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('2-11', false)">2.11</span> of the General Terms and Conditions being fulfilled.</li>
					<li id="4-5"><b>4.5.</b> If the Passenger is liable to pay any legal fee due to the cancellation, the Service Provider shall be entitled to claim a commission on the amount of this fee.</li>
					<li><b>4.6.</b> The Service Provider shall be entitled to issue an electronic invoice at its discretion, provided that the technical conditions for this are met.</li>
					<li><b>4.7.</b> The Customer shall pay the invoice by the due date indicated on the invoice, failing which the Service Provider shall charge interest on arrears at the rate of twice the base rate of the central bank of the Republic of Slovenia per month, and the Customer shall bear the costs of collection in the event of late payment of invoices.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Data and confidentiality protection, protection of personal rights</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-5">
    				<li><b>5.1.</b> The parties shall treat as trade secrets, in accordance with the provisions of the law in force, all facts, information, data and solutions arising from their activities which are in the public domain in connection with the present legal relationship, except as provided for in point <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('5-2', false)">5.2.</span></li>
					<li id="5-2"><b>5.2.</b> The provision of information by the Service Provider to guests or third parties other than the guest from the visitor, as defined in clause <span class="click-click" onclick="focusOnObject('2-3', false)">2.3.</span> of the General Terms and Conditions, shall not constitute a breach of a trade secret.</li>
					<li><b>5.3.</b> The Service Provider shall take reasonable care to ensure that no unauthorized third party is able to modify the content of the public data uploaded by the Customer.</li>
					<li><b>5.4.</b> The Service Provider shall take reasonable care to ensure that unauthorized third parties cannot modify the content of public data uploaded by the Customer.</li>
					<li><b>5.5.</b> The Provider is entitled to record and store the IP address and other technical data of the Customer in its system.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Liability, enforcement of a warranty claim</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-6">
    				<li><b>6.1</b> The Service Provider, in view of the fact that it receives a commission for table bookings, shall not be liable to the Customer for the result.
					In the event of no or, in the opinion of the Provider, an insufficient number of standard reservations being received in respect of a table of accommodation uploaded by the Customer, the Customer shall not be entitled to any legal compensation in the event of the Provider's contractual performance. The service provider is not responsible for the appearance in the search engine of the table of flats or for its nonappearance, if it is the consequence of the incomplete data filled in by the customer.</li>
					<li><b>6.2</b> The service provider is not liable for damages caused by the guest to the customer or other 3. person, in particular for the actual non-use of the apartment table, and for violation of the conditions of use.</li>
					<li><b>6.3</b> The Service Provider shall not be liable for any claim of the passenger or other third party against the customer, for any deviation of the characteristics of the table and the related service from the data uploaded by the customer, and for the accuracy of the uploaded data. The changes and modifications to the menu of the restaurant in the meantime, but not registered in the administrative interface, the responsibility for the changes and modifications shall be borne solely by the operator.</li>
					<li><b>6.4</b> The service provider informs the customer that any objections to this legal relationship in person at the registered office of the service provider in the contract or electronically at any of the contact details provided . The service provider informs the customer that he can exercise his warranty in the event of defective performance in accordance with the provisions of Â§ 305-311 / A of the PTK (rules on warranty and warranty).</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Modification and termination of the Contract</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-7">
    				<li><b>7.1</b> The Service Provider informs the Customer that the General Terms and Conditions may be amended unilaterally, if necessary, in accordance with Article 205/A (1) of the P.T.C., subject to the provisions of the law. If the Customer wishes to deviate from the General Terms and Conditions, he shall be entitled to notify the Service Provider in writing as an offer to amend the contract.</li>
					<li><b>7.2</b> The service contract may be terminated by mutual agreement of the parties, by ordinary termination, by extraordinary termination (for any private act in breach of the contract), and - in the cases and under the conditions laid down in the applicable legislation - by withdrawal.</li>
					<li><b>7.3</b> The Parties may terminate the contract by unilateral written declaration with 1 day's notice, -electronically .</li>
					<li><b>7.4</b> Even a single breach of the obligations contained in the contract shall be considered a serious breach of contract. This shall in itself constitute grounds for immediate termination of the contract by means of a written declaration addressed to the other party, without giving reasons or with reasons (electronically).</li>
					<li><b>7.5</b> If the Customer is deemed to be a consumer under the legislation in force, the Service Provider shall inform the Customer that the provisions of the Act No. 17/1999 ( II.5 (1) of the Government Decree No. 17/1999 (1) of the Government of the Republic of Poland on the Contract of Contractors who are absent from the contract without giving any reason, provided that the Supplier has not commenced performance of the contract within this period with the consent of the Customer. The Customer may exercise this right from the date on which the contract is concluded, and shall not be liable for any further costs in connection with the transaction.</li>
					<li><b>7.6</b> Upon termination of the service contract, the parties shall settle their accounts with each other.</li>
    			</ul>
    		</li>
    		<li><span class="fejezet-cim">Miscellaneous and Final Provisions</span>
    			<ul class="fejezet" id="fejezet-8">
    				<li><b>8.1.</b> The legal relationship shall be deemed to have commenced immediately if the following conditions are met in full and in combination: the online completion of the registration data and the confirmation of the registration by e-mail link and acceptance of the general terms and conditions.</li>
					<li><b>8.2.</b> The service contract is concluded for an indefinite period of time, unless otherwise stated, with the service provider informing the customer that the shortest period of time is 1 working day.</li>
					<li><b>8.3.</b> The parties shall settle any disputes arising by amicable means, in the absence of which the exclusive jurisdiction of the Buda District Court or the Somogy County Court shall be stipulated.</li>
					<li><b>8.4.</b> In matters not regulated in this contract, the laws in force at the time of the conclusion of the contract shall prevail.</li>
					<li><b>8.5.</b> The Customer acknowledges that the sale of special surfaces, the ordering of translations or the use of other services beyond the above shall be subject to the provisions of these GTC, with the understanding that the current price of these special services shall be indicated separately and that a separate request is required for ordering.</li>
